urnament|NCAA]] Runners-up\n|-\n| 1991\n| Ray Ratelle\n| 31\u20134\n| 14\u20132\n| 2nd\n| '''[[1991 NCAA Division I Men's Volleyball Tournament|NCAA]] Champions\n|-\n| 1992\n| Ray Ratelle\n| 27\u20134\n| 15\u20131\n| 1st\n|\n|-\n{{CBB Yearly Record Subhead|\n|name=\n|startyear=1993\n|conference=''[[Mountain Pacific Sports Federation]]''\n|endyear=2017\n|}}\n|-\n| 1993\n| Ray Ratelle\n| 18\u201313\n| 12\u20137\n| 2nd\n|\n|-\n| 1994\n| Ray Ratelle\n| 13\u201315\n| 7\u201312\n| 5th\n|\n|-\n| 1995\n| Ray Ratelle\n| 18\u20139\n| 12\u20137\n| 3rd\n|\n|-\n| 1996\n| Ray Ratelle\n| 21\u20136\n| 15\u20134\n| 2nd\n|\n|-\n| 1997\n| Ray Ratelle\n| 19\u201310\n| 12\u20137\n| 2nd\n|\n|-\n| 1998\n| Ray Ratelle\n| 22\u20137\n| 13\u20136\n| 2nd\n|\n|-\n| 1999\n| Ray Ratelle\n| 22\u20134\n| 17\u20132\n| 1st\n| [[1999 NCAA Division I Men's Volleyball Tournament|NCAA]] Runners-up\n|-\n| 2000\n| Ray Ratelle\n| 23\u20135\n| 16\u20133\n| 1st\n|\n|-\n| 2001\n| Alan Knipe\n| 18\u20137\n| 12\u20135\n| 1st\n|\n|-\n| 2002\n| Alan Knipe\n| 13\u201318\n| 9\u201313\n| 7th\n|\n|-\n| 2003\n| Alan Knipe\n| 17\u201313\n| 11\u201311\n| 8th\n|\n|-\n| 2004\n| Alan Knipe\n| 28\u20137\n| 18\u20134\n| 2nd\n| [[2004 NCAA Division I Men's Volleyball Tournament|NCAA]] Runners-up\n|-\n| 2005\n| Alan Knipe\n| 22\u201310\n| 14\u20138\n| 5th\n|\n|-\n| 2006\n| Alan Knipe\n| 22\u201310\n| 14\u20138\n| 4th\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| Alan Knipe\n| 11\u201317\n| 6\u201316\n| 10th\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| Alan Knipe\n| 23\u20137\n| 18\u20134\n| 1st\n| [[2008 NCAA Division I Men's Volleyball Tournament|NCAA]] Final Four\n|-\n| 2009\n| Alan Knipe\n| 14\u201314\n| 11\u201311\n| 7th\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| Andy Read\n| 12\u201317\n| 8\u201314\n| 10th\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| Andy Read\n| 15\u201314\n| 12\u201310\n| 6th\n|\n|-\n{{CBB Yearly Record Entry \n| championship = confboth\n| season = 2011\n| name = Andy Read\n| overall = 15\u201314\n| conference = 12\u201310\n| confstanding = 6th\n| postseason = \n}} \n{{CBB Yearly Record Entry \n| championship